VRM Program Development – Cyturus Skip to content Home About ARM CRT Services CMMC Readiness Baseline Vendor Risk Management Program Development BC DR Cloud Strategy Business Impact Analysis Identity & Access Management Industries Contact Menu Home About ARM CRT Services CMMC Readiness Baseline Vendor Risk Management Program Development BC DR Cloud Strategy Business Impact Analysis Identity & Access Management Industries Contact VRM Program Development Vendor Risk Management (VRM) Organizations implement VRM programs as a formal way to evaluate, track and measure risk, assess its impact on all aspects of your business, and develop compensating controls or other forms of mitigation to lessen the impact on the business if something should A formal VRM program provides consistency for managing vendors and establishes a methodology to share risk information about them within your Vendor Management Charter and Policy Review Vendor management needs to be treated as a continuous program in order to be Articulating and documenting an executive leadership approved vendor management charter will establish enterprise expectations, define success criteria, and will serve as the guidepost for successfully developing a Vendor Management Risk A full review of the current Vendor Management Policies will be performed, and recommendations presented for their In addition, we will assist in the creation and subsequent approval for standard provisions that every contract should contain related to cyber Vendor Framework - Topology and Categorization The vendor framework effort will create the definitions for the vendor categorization and associated topology framework for managing all In addition, this exercise will establish the risk criteria by which a vendor is placed into one of the four categories Critical, High, Medium and This includes the creation of a roadmap framework to manage the contract termination renewal dates and an action plan to update the contracts with the standard provisions on or near a contract event Risk Register Cyturus will assist in establishing a Risk A Risk Register is a tool for documenting risks to the business, categorizing by response strategy (Avoidance, Transferring, Mitigation, Acceptance) and the actions to manage and maintain the current status for each of the identified The Risk Register is essential to the successful management of organizational Our VRM service is based on our proprietary Adaptive Risk Model (ARM) The Cyturus ARM identifies deficiencies, measures potential business impact, and recommends prioritized remediation actions across the entire This service can be ingested into the Cyturus ARM framework for deeper examination and lateral impact as part of a future holistic Does your organization have a formal VRM program? Canavan Disease Treatment - Myrtelle, Home About Team Pipeline Technology Canavan Disease Clinical Trial News Canavan Disease Myrtelle’s clinical trial for Canavan disease received FDA clearance to begin Phase 1 2 in December of The clinical program is the first gene therapy to target oligodendrocytes, with Orphan Drug Designation Our first patient was dosed in April OUR MISSION Redefining the Way We Target and Treat Canavan Disease Through our core technologies, assets, patents and expertise, we have built a platform to address Canavan Myrtelle’s Canavan gene therapy (rAAV-Olig001-ASPA) is the first gene therapy designed to target the oligodendrocytes, which are critical for myelination and nerve Improvement of ASPA function in these cells reduces concentrations of (NAA), allowing myelination to Our Timeline PRECURSORS studies investigate the ability to deliver the ASPA gene HUMAN CLINICAL TRIALS First ever human clinical study of ASPA gene delivery begins outside of the US, with delivery developed by Paola Leone and USA CLINICAL STUDY Human clinical study of ASPA gene delivery extended to the AAV2 First ever human clinical study of ASPA gene replacement with AAV2 vector begins based on technologies developed by Paola Leone and NATURAL HISTORY Canavan natural history data assembled by Paola Leone and TARGETING Novel AAV derived enabling specific Novel AAVs (rAAV-Oligo) DATA AGGREGATION data with developed to support human clinical IND USA IND opened for gene therapy clinical FIRST PATIENT DOSED First patients treated in clinical study of ASPA gene replacement specifically targeting Canavan Disease: At a Glance Overview Canavan disease (CD) is a rare genetic neurological disorder characterized by spongy degeneration of the white matter in the Genetic Origins Canavan is caused by mutations in the gene encoding the enzyme aspartoacylase (ASPA), a critical enzyme for healthy white matter development and Incidence Estimates of the incidence of Canavan range from as high as 1:6,400 to 1:100,000 live births in various populations around the Disease Onset Affected infants may appear normal at birth, but usually develop symptoms by six months of Symptoms Motor function is severely impaired at birth and invariably worsens over Additional symptoms include, poor head control, eye tracking difficulty, excessive irritability, abnormally large head size, delays in motor and developmental Progressive symptoms include, seizures, spasticity, difficulties in swallowing and overall muscle complications usually occur by years of Treatment & Cure There are no cures or disease modifying drugs for The only drugs available to date are palliative, including antiepileptic and antispasmodic Stay Connected Learn More Understanding Gene Therapy for Canavan Disease Download Brochure Contact Tel: Email HQ Edgewater Place Suite Wakefield, MA Join Our Community Sign up to receive Myrtelle news and Email © by Myrtelle   Proprietary Technology & Intellectual Property - Myrtelle, Home About Team Technology Canavan Disease Clinical Trial News TECHNOLOGY Myrtelle is advancing proprietary technologies to optimize the delivery of genes to cells, enabling innovative approaches to address the needs of hundreds of disorders involving LEAD PLATFORM Myrtelle is developing a vector, called to deliver a therapeutic ASPA gene directly to the oligodendrocyte cells that are responsible for producing myelin to restore the ability of oligodendrocytes to make the ASPA enzyme on their The ASPA gene is delivered directly into the fluid that surrounds the brain and spinal cord (cerebrospinal fluid), allowing the gene therapy to reach many The gene is packaged using a unique virus (AAV) vector that targets The virus is inactive and cannot cause Once the ASPA gene is inside the cells, researchers believe it may help the cells make and release Aspartoacylase (ASPA), the enzyme needed to breakdown (NAA). Jobs - Clubhouse Join the Clubhouse team Clubhouse is a new type of social product based on It allows people everywhere to talk, tell stories, develop ideas, deepen friendships, and meet interesting new people around the We launched in private beta two months ago, and the response has been very Our early users love the product and we have been featured in publications like The New York Times, Forbes, The Telegraph, TechCrunch, The Information, CNBC, and WIRED — as well as a huge range of thoughtful blog posts . Today, we are a small and productive team with a strong background in consumer We studied engineering at Stanford, built early products at Google and Pinterest, and have founded and sold multiple We are well funded, with recent backing from VCs and many of the best angel investors in Silicon As we look towards a broader release of Clubhouse, we are seeking to add a few extraordinary people to our core team in both and 📱iOS Engineer 🔮Community Success 🛡️Trust & Safety Senior Analyst 🧰Operations Program Manager Home ・ Jobs ・ Privacy ・ Terms ・ Guidelines   Check 1, 2, Is this thing on? - Clubhouse 🎙 Check 1, 2, Is this thing on? July , It’s been just over three months since we started building Clubhouse and shared the early beta with a few At the time, the app was very rough and we didn’t know what to Our goal was to collect feedback, quietly iterate, and avoid making noise until we felt the product was ready for For a number of reasons, the “build quietly” approach didn’t We are hugely grateful that people seem to care about the product and we’ve learned a lot from the feedback—both good and Given all that’s been said, we wanted to share a bit of our early thinking on Clubhouse, our gratitude for the community and our plans for the future, so people understand how we’re approaching building this Thank you for reading! 🙏🏽 What is Clubhouse? Clubhouse is a new type of network based on When you open the app you can see “rooms” full of people talking—all open so you can hop in and out, exploring different You enter each room as an audience member, but if you want to talk you just raise your hand, and the speakers can choose to invite you Or you can create a room of your It’s a place to meet with friends and with new people around the world—to tell stories, ask questions, debate, learn, and have impromptu conversations on thousands of different Clubhouse is , and we think voice is a very special With no camera on, you don’t have to worry about eye contact, what you’re wearing, or where you You can talk on Clubhouse while you’re folding laundry, breastfeeding, commuting, working on your couch in the basement, or going for a Instead of typing something and hitting Send, you’re engaged in a dialogue with The intonation, inflection and emotion conveyed through voice allow you to pick up on nuance and form uniquely human connections with You can still challenge each other and have tough conversations—but with voice there is often an ability to build more This is what drew us to the Over the past three months on Clubhouse, people have shared their joy and dismay about Supreme Court decisions, their feelings of anger and helplessness over the murder of George Floyd, and their struggles navigating the challenges of home and work during There have been rooms with people from all walks of life finding common We’ve seen people host book clubs, fireside chats, passionate debates, and comedy When people have fallen asleep late at night, others in the room have “tucked them in”—quietly sending them back to the audience in order to mute their People seem to be coming back because it’s a place where they can talk for hours at a time and leave each day feeling better rather than worse, because they’ve deepened friendships, built new ones, and learned something Why isn’t it open to the public yet? We are building Clubhouse for everyone and working to make it available to the world as quickly as It’s not intended to be exclusive we just aren’t ready to ship the general release version There are two reasons for this: First, we think it’s important to grow communities slowly, rather than the user base This helps ensure that things don’t break, keeps the composition of the community diverse, and allows us to tune the product as it Second, we are a small team, and we haven’t yet finished building the features that will allow us to handle more Right now the two of us are the only We’ve benefitted from the support of many, and are actively hiring , but between infrastructure scaling, feature development, gathering product feedback, and general company building, there haven’t been many spare hours in the Plus we have four young kids between us jumping on our keyboards as we type! 😅 So what’s next? Before we can move from a beta to a general release we want to ensure that the product can handle more Among other things, this means having robust community policies and tools to ensure that people have a great experience as the user bas

What makes AfterShoot different from other AI culling apps? As compared to other Culling apps that aim to provide incremental improvements to your workflow, AfterShoot aims to do it for you while still letting you retain the entire control over the selections . Yes AfterShoot can automatically identify the file format (raw jpeg) and assign star and colors to the For JPEGs, it stores these in the ITPC metadata whereas for raws, it does so in the XMP Installation and Updates How do I update my copy of AfterShoot? CI CD integrations | Infracost Menu Docs Docs Menu Getting started Supported resources Cost estimation of resources CI CD integrations Getting support FAQ CI CD integrations GitHub Action # The Infracost GitHub Action can be used to automatically add a pull request comment showing the cost estimate difference (similar to git diff ) between a pull request and the master branch whenever Terraform files GitLab CI # The Infracost GitLab CI template can be used to automatically add a merge request comment showing the cost estimate difference (similar to git diff ) between a pull request and the master CircleCI # Please check this for our and subscribe to this GitHub issue for Edit this page Previous Â« Cost estimation of resources Next Getting support Â» GitHub Action GitLab CI CircleCI Docs Getting started Integrations Getting support Community Discord GitHub More Twitter Copyright Â© Infracost   Getting started | Infracost Menu Docs Docs Menu Getting started Supported resources Cost estimation of resources CI CD integrations Getting support FAQ Getting started Infracost shows hourly and monthly cost estimates for a Terraform This helps users quickly see the cost breakdown and compare different deployment options The Infracost GitHub Action or GitLab CI template can be used to automatically add a PR comment showing the cost estimate diff between a pull merge request and the master Installation # Install the latest Infracost release: macOS (Homebrew) macOS (manual) Linux Docker Copy brew install infracost Use our free hosted API for cloud prices by registering for an API key: Copy infracost register The INFRACOST_API_KEY environment variable can be used to set the API key in CI If you prefer, you can run your own Cloud Pricing API . Run Infracost using our example Terraform project to see how it You can also play with the file in the example: Copy git clone https: github.com infracost example-terraform.git infracost --tfdir aws Usage methods # Infracost can be run with different options depending on the , for example: Terraform directory # This is the default Point to the Terraform directory using --tfdir and pass any required Terraform flags using --tfflags . Internally Infracost runs Terraform init , plan and show init requires cloud credentials to be set, via the usual AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID environment This method works with remote state Copy infracost --tfdir path to code --tfflags "-var-file=myvars.tfvars" Terraform state file # Point to the Terraform directory using --tfdir and instruct Infracost to use the Terraform state file using --use-tfstate . This implies that you have already run Terraform init , thus Infracost just runs Terraform show , which does not require cloud creds to be This method takes less time to run compared with method #1 and also works with remote Copy terraform init infracost --tfdir path to code --use-tfstate Terraform plan JSON # Point to an existing Terraform plan JSON file using --tfjson . This implies that the user has already run Terraform init , thus Infracost just runs Terraform show , which does not require cloud creds to be Copy cd path to code terraform init terraform plan . terraform show infracost --tfjson Terraform plan file # Point to the Terraform directory and use the Terraform This implies that the user has already run Terraform init , thus Infracost just runs Terraform show , which does not require cloud creds to be This method works with remote state Copy cd path to code terraform init terraform plan . infracost --tfdir path to code --tfplan Useful options # Run infracost --help to see the available options, which include: Copy --output value Output format (json, table) (default: "table") --show-skipped Show unsupported resources, some of which might be free (default: false) --no-color Turn off colored output (default: false) Environment variables # INFRACOST_API_KEY : Infracost API key, run infracost register to get TERRAFORM_BINARY : used to change the path to the terraform binary: Copy TERRAFORM_BINARY=~ bin terraform_0.13 infracost --tfdir path to code INFRACOST_SKIP_UPDATE_CHECK=true : can be useful in CI CD systems to skip the Infracost update INFRACOST_LOG_LEVEL : can be set to warn in CI CD systems to reduce Standard Terraform environment variables such as TF_ can also be added if required, for example: Copy TF_CLI_CONFIG_FILE="$HOME .terraformrc-custom" infracost --tfdir path to code Terragrunt users # Please subscribe to this GitHub issue for updates as we re working on Terraform Cloud users # Infracost supports Terraform Cloud, AWS S3 or other remote state If you use Terraform Cloud with Remote Execution Mode, please subscribe to this GitHub issue for updates as we re working on supporting it Edit this page Next Supported resources Â» Installation Usage methods Terraform directory Terraform state file Terraform plan JSON Terraform plan file Useful options Environment variables Terragrunt users Terraform Cloud users Docs Getting started Integrations Gettin

Boardroom Adds Support for the Synthetix Spartan Council - Saasy - Webflow HTML Website Template Delegates SDK Dashboard Updates Boardroom Adds Support for the Synthetix Spartan Council Kevin Nielsen December , The Spartan Council, responsible for approving proposed changes to the Synthetix protocol, can now be elected and overseen on the Boardroom platform The Synthetix community has always been at the forefront of DeFi innovation, and the recent effort to structure its governance with a vision for a Synthetix Spartan Council proves to be just another prime example of a novel mechanism to evolve and scale protocol The election for Spartan Council members just went live . Over the last two weeks, nineteen members of the Synthetix community have nominated themselves to be on the Spartan Council, a new component of Synthetix governance, and seven will be voted on successfully for the first Council Epoch, the month of The Council will be responsible for approving proposed changes to the Synthetix Initially, this will only include SCCPs (i.e. configurable changes, such as changing exchange rates or the target ), but the aim is to also include SIPs (i.e. more complex changes to the protocol) in the All of this and more can be explored on the Boardroom Synthetix Hub Hereâs a quick summary of the new framework from Kainâs post : A new Snapshot instance will be created This instance will have an proposal to elect seven council members Voting weight will be based on a users debt at the last fee period Voting weight will be scaled quadratically The seven highest vote weights will be the elected council Council members can be removed via token holders modifying their votes Every three months a new election will be held for the Spartan Council The seven council members will then vote directly on SCCPs under these conditions: One council member one vote If the constitution of the council changes during a proposal it is invalidated if it would have changed the result Proposals require a minimum of three positive votes to pass The minimum proposal length is hours The pDAO can require a revote at its discretion The number of seats can be modified via SCCP To learn more you can read this SIP written by Andy In this effort, the Boardroom team is excited to support the community and the newly elected council members as they look to formalize this process and reach a more efficient deliberation and voting mechanism for SCCP s and in the future, SIPâs: The Boardroom Synthetix Hub Features: A basic governance landing page displaying the nomination proposal, recent and upcoming SCCPs on which council members vote, and the list of current council members or A proposal details page mirror Snapshotâs UI, displaying relevant information, and allowing the user to cast their vote from this same A voter information profile page featuring delegate (or a nomineeâs) information, social links, associated addresses, and a delegation â We feel itâs important that delegates have the tools and information they need to properly represent their constituents, and that SNX token holders remain informed in order to act as an accountability mechanism should the council members deviate from their mandate as community Transparency in information can create a useful balance with managerial efficiency existing alongside community and voter Governing anything, including decentralised protocols, is obviously and within the Synthetix community we have a strong norm of running low risk experiments to attempt to optimise aspects of the system, this proposal is intended to be aligned with that - Kain Warwick We will be collecting all feedback on the Boardroom Discord #Feedback Make sure you also sign up for the Boardroom Product Newsletter to stay up to date with the latest releases and announcements! Hera Biotech – Advancing the Standard of Care in Women s Health We Are HERA BIOTECH About HERA Biotech Our Vision To be the world leader in understanding & addressing diagnostic and therapeutic deficiencies in women s Our Philosophy We are building a collaborative driven to advancing the standard of care in women s Our Mission Relentlessly seek to understand the root cause of diseases in women s health, thereby, uncovering new ways of diagnosing and treating them About Us Who We Are Hera Biotech, was formed to apply advances in biotechnology to address unmet needs in the field of women’s health and specifically, in reproductive Hera began operations in January of as a Delaware “C” Corporation with headquarters in San Antonio, Hera’s initial goal is to commercialize the MetriDx™, a novel, method for the definitive and early diagnosis of Meet the Team - Coming soon Frequently Ask Question How We Fight Endometriosis What is Endometriosis? According to the Mayo Clinic, “Endometriosis is an disorder in which tissue similar to the tissue that normally lines the inside of your uterus – the endometrium – grows outside your ” Endometriosis often involves other pelvic organs and, in some cases, can spread elsewhere in the Despite no longer being inside of the uterus, endometrial tissue continues to function in the same way it would in the This means it thickens, breaks down and bleeds with each menstrual cycle however, this tissue has no way to exit the body and becomes This trapped tissue can cause cysts, surrounding tissue can become irritated and, eventually, scar tissue and adhesions can cause pelvic tissues and organs to stick to each Further, endometriosis can cause pain, often times severe, especially during menstrual Common symptoms associated with endometriosis are painful periods, pain with intercourse, pain with bowel movements or urination, excessive bleeding, infertility, fatigue, diarrhea, constipation, bloating or Endometriosis is estimated to effect % of women, aged worldwide million in the The average time a woman in the goes before receiving an endometriosis diagnosis is One of the largest contributing factors to the length of time it takes for a woman to receive a diagnosis from the time she develops symptoms is because the current method for definitive diagnosis of endometriosis is visualization during laparoscopic surgery, confirmed by histological pathology, which fails to confirm diagnosis ~50% of the Estimated Economic Impact of Endometriosis In the US, the annual economic burden of endometriosis due to direct medical care of endometriosis is estimated at ~$80B a cost that could be dramatically curtailed with accurate, early and 5 Hera’s breakthrough approach is based on cutting edge, single cell, analysis to identify biological This approach enables clinicians to definitively diagnose endometriosis regardless of stage with unparalleled Our Approach to Diagnosis The patient’s endometrial cells are collected during an procedure, thereby eliminating the need for surgical The initial MetriDx™ configuration utilizes analysis of single cells obtained from a uterine pipelle brush MetriDx™ will bring unprecedented diagnostic capability to physicians, lower liability risk within hospitals, eliminate unnecessary surgical procedures and reduce the considerable time patients typically suffer before receiving a diagnosis, all the while maintaining tissue collection and a direct pathology About MetriDx™ The initial pathway for commercialization will be the development of MetriDx™ as a laboratory developed test (LDT, or “home brew”) following the necessary validation studies and obtaining a CPT®PLA (Proprietary Laboratory Analyses) code for This would enable the company to conduct endometriosis testing from a central CLIA lab operated by the The initial target market for Hera is the patients seeking reproductive assistance through fertility clinics or reproductive As endometriosis is the number one cause of female infertility, the MetriDxTM can be utilized as a screening test to ensure that underlying endometriosis can be resolved prior to starting Knowing the your Endo status prior to beginning an intervention can save couples thousand of dollars on interventions that have little chance of success without resolution of the underlying Further, resolving underlying Endo prior to intervention will also boost the success rates of the physicians and clinics administering Lastly, this patient population is accustomed to cash pay, as only 1 3 of women in the US have any insurance coverage for reproductive This will allow Hera to begin selling prior to receiving our reimbursement Following execution of this revenue model, the company will focus it’s attention on marketing the MetriDxTM™ to OB GYNs as a diagnostic tool to utilize in their Hera Biotech has a highly capable and experienced team and is raising a round of $2.0M to initiate and complete the proof of concept trial and refine the parameters of the Helpin

T cells are generated in vivo by administering proprietary activated autologous macrophages that activate tumoricidal T Cells, Neutrophils, and Natural Killer Cells whilst curtailing the activity of Tregs, MDSCs, & T cells are generated ex vivo by in vitro expansion of T lymphocytes (TIL). Both in vivo and ex vivo methods result in a polyclonal immune response against multiple tumor The therapy has broad applicability for unmet needs in the treatment of solid Rather than directly targeting tumors through individual , SIRPant generates a , multifaceted immune response against tumors, thereby acting as a cancer This approach targets many antigens resulting in the production of T cells and B cells that lead to SIRPant is synergistic with Radiation Therapy, showcasing complete response and abscopal effects, as well as Immune Checkpoint Blockade, with complete response in L pancreatic and colorectal Check back often for updates on our ongoing research, or contact one of our principals for more information . Building a Pixel Art Bitcoin Tracker - Tidbyt Blog Community About Pixlet Building a Pixel Art Bitcoin Tracker October , ByÂ Mats Linander apps for fun & profit We ve been working on Tidbyt for about a year Developing the individual apps that run on the platform is a big part of what s made the project Today, we re happy to be able to share some of that joy! Pixlet is the open source version of our internal app development It makes it pretty darn simple to build pixel In our production environment, Pixlet is running 7 behind the scenes to power everything on Tidbyt from stock prices or weather information to tracking the NYCÂ In this guide, I ll walk you through how to build a Bitcoin price What is this thing? Pixlet is a interface that runs and renders Pixlet The scripts are written in a language that s very similar to They can use Pixlet s library of "widgets" for laying out and drawing The result of running a script is a GIF or WebP animation, which can be viewed in a browser or "pushed" to a Tidbyt device via the Tidbyt Down the road, we hope to fully open up our systems to allow Pixlet apps to be published and made available to other A picture and some code This Bitcoin tracker is fully implemented with It fetches the current price of a Bitcoin (in USD) and displays it on a Tidbyt You might be surprised by how simple the code To get started, let s install Pixlet and make sure you are able to run Check out the installation instructions if you re using If you re on macOSÂ and have Homebrew installed, you should be able to just run: brew install tidbyt tidbyt pixlet Once you have Pixlet installed, create a file named and write a simple Hello World script: load("render.star", "render") def main(): return ( child = ("Hello, World!") ) â If you ve installed Pixlet correctly, you should be able to execute this script with: $ pixlet serve --watch Browse to http: localhost:8080 and you should see a "Hello, World!" Getting Bitcoin data To get closer to a truly useful app, we ll be pulling in some Bitcoin CoinDesk s Bitcoin Price Index API is free to use and requires no We ll use the http module to retrieve the Pixlet includes several modules from the Starlib This is sort of a standard library for Starlark (the langauge that Pixlet scripts are written in), and it s very handy when building anything but the simplest Update your to get actual Bitcoin data: load("render.star", "render") load("http.star", "http") COINDESK_PRICE_URL = "https: api.coindesk.com v1 bpi currentprice.json" def main(): rep = (COINDESK_PRICE_URL) if != : fail("Coindesk request failed with status %d", ) rate = ()["bpi"]["USD"]["rate_float"] return ( child = ("BTC: %d USD" % rate) ) â Save the file and refresh your You should now see the live price of VoilÃ . A perfectly functional Bitcoin price Adding an icon To make our applet a bit snazzier, I went over to Pixilart and drew this simple Bitcoin icon: Pixlet allows us to embed graphics in our scripts through the Image We ll use the encoding base64 module to embed the image in our source Finally, we ll use the Row Widget to lay out the icon and the price of Bitcoin, : load("render.star", "render") load("http.star", "http") load("encoding base64.star", "base64") COINDESK_PRICE_URL = "https: api.coindesk.com v1 bpi currentprice.json" # Load Bitcoin icon from base64 encoded data BTC_ICON = (""" iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABEAAAARCAYAAAA7bUf6AAAAlklEQVQ4T2NkwAH+H2T jy7FaP+ TEZtyDEG4Zi0TTPXXzoDF0A1DMQRsADbN6MZdO4NiENwQbAbERh1lWLzMmgFGo5iFZBDYEFwuwG sISCPUIKyGgDRjAyBXYXMNIz5XgDQga8TpLboYgux8DO AwoUuLiEqTLBFMcmxQ7V0gssgklIsL AYozjsoBoE45OZi5DRBSnkCAMLhlPBiQGHlAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC """) def main(): rep = (COINDESK_PRICE_URL) if != : fail("CoinDesk request failed with status %d", ) rate = ()["bpi"]["USD"]["rate_float"] return ( child = ( # Row lays out its children horizontally children = [ (src=BTC_ICON), ("$%d" % rate), ], ) ) This clearly leaves something to be desired as far as layout is concerned, but the individual elements (the icon and the price) aren t too shabby! Beautification By default, Row will pack its children as closely together as it possibly That s often a useful behaviour, but in this case perhaps not so We can instruct Row to use as much horizontal space as possible by passing expanded=True , and then use the main_align and cross_align parameters to adjust how the children are spaced For details on these parameters, check out the full Widget reference . We ll also place the Row itself in a Box to ensure that it s placed in the vertical center of the Box actually centers horizontally as well, but since our Row is expanded that won t Don t worry if all this alignment stuff feels a bit confusing at It ll be a lot clearer when you ve had a chance to play around with load("render.star", "render") load("http.star", "http") load("encoding base64.star", "base64") load("cache.star", "cache") COINDESK_PRICE_URL = "https: api.coindesk.com v1 bpi currentprice.json" BTC_ICON = (""" iVBORw0KGgoAAAA

was a transformative year for many, and it brought about some exciting and unique ideas – Hiveclass being one of Flashback to the beginning of , the whole world took a mandatory, forced The Beginning Every single person on the planet was affected in one way or another by the pandemic, children Educators were forced to quickly pivot and reimagine instruction in a few short weeks, and kids started spending 6+ hours per day in front of a Although sports are slowly coming back, recent studies show that an alarming number of kids have no interest in returning to the activities they were involved in These issues are what inspired three close friends to come together and decide that they were going to solve the problem of keeping kids active through remote The Problem The United States ranks #1 in childhood obesity – not a statistic to be proud With an increase in time spent in front of a screen due to the pandemic, it’s alarming to picture where this level of inactivity will In the last years, the world has dramatically Kids are more likely to talk to each other on messaging apps, share information via social networks and daydream over content shaped by marketing and advertising Kids needs to learn to play The Solution Hiveclass is so much more than a mobile platform – through endless hours of conversation and research, our team realized that youth sports training and physical activity for kids is not what it used to be or where it needs to We aim to provide a better resource to kids who spend nearly six hours per day online by producing captivating educational content so they can learn new skills, master unique tricks and connect with their peers in their own time and at their own Technology and screens aren’t going anywhere – it’s up to us to work towards turning passive scrolling into Active Screen Ready to Join? Conferences Events and News Investors Compliance Orders Contact Search Search Search for: Stratus Facebook Stratus LinkedIn Stratus Twitter Site Overlay Physicians Nimbus Overview Nimbus was invented by an interventional pain management physician that wanted a cost effective, easy to use, RF cannula that would provide a large and optimally shaped lesion for treating chronic pain patients in After tremendous effort and significant investment into the design, testing, validation, IP and regulatory clearances, Nimbus was Busy interventional pain management practitioners appreciate the simplicity and efficiency of Nimbus to treat both simple and complex RF targets for Nimbus provides a large – prolate spheroid lesion 4 that minimizes technical obstacles and allows a simple perpendicular 5 or “down the beam” Nimbus has been shown to significantly decrease procedural time 2 , which opens up procedure rooms for additional patient treatments and provides improved revenue opportunity to the hospitals and surgery centers where Nimbus is Nimbus enables the interventional pain management practitioners to place the cannula perpendicular 5 to a target and create a large field lesion volume with a single Whether the target is “down the beam”, for example medial branch or is a cephalocaudal running nerve, for example genicular or sympathetic chain Nimbus creates a proper lesion When compared to other large volume RF techniques such as internally cooled electrodes, Nimbus is more cost effective, efficient, easy to use and requires no special Nimbus is the only large lesion RF device for pain with MRI validation 5 of lesion size (601.7mm 3 ). Method — Atlast 0 Skip to Content About Current Page: Method MY Super Ingredient Open Menu Close Menu About Current Page: Method MY Super Ingredient Open Menu Close Menu About Current Page: Method MY Super Ingredient There’s a method to our madness How do mushrooms taste like meat? It sounds crazy, but here’s how it Basically, we have these big indoor farms where we’re able to recreate the conditions that mycelium needs to grow By using solid state fermentation, the mycelium can grow into any This farming process allows us to create MY super ingredient, or what’s known by mycology nerds like us as aerial Unlike other meats, which are extruded and highly processed, this is a whole structure which means there’s almost zero Our super ingredient tastes like meat because the mycelium fibers grow together in a tissue that resembles the network of muscle tissues in animals (therefore mimicking its texture as well). From spore to slab, the entire process only takes around ten Our Method Seed Our process starts by seeding gourmet mushrooms into trays filled with a nutrient rich medium to grow Grow The trays are placed into vertical farms that simulate the same conditions that mycelium grows in Harvest In a matter of days, the mycelium is harvested and ready to use as a raw ingredient for meatless Cool, but why is this revolutionary? Historically, fungi is hard to find (See Forager’s Secret) . Mushrooms take a long time to grow and nature is finicky when it comes to creating the ideal conditions for them to (That’s why rare and mushrooms are so expensive!) Our farming method is pretty amazing — and granted we’re biased — not only because it allows us to tap into an ancient organism, which is massively beneficial to our entire ecosystem, and makes mycelium taste like delicious meat, but also because it allows us to unlock nature’s brilliance in a way that’s scalable and By not slaughtering animals or using excess land or engineering nature to do something that’s, well, not in its nature, we’re able to support all life on earth, which is pretty revolutionary when you think about Imagine the Impact Learn about our Ethos Ethos In the News Media Kit Team Careers Partner Blog Contact FAQs Privacy | Terms © Atlast   Atlast 0 Skip to Content About Method MY Super Ingredient Open Menu Close Menu About Method MY Super Ingredient Open Menu Close Menu About Method MY Super Ingredient Ethos In the News Media Kit Team Careers Partner Blog Contact FAQs Privacy | Terms © Atlast   MY Super Ingredient — Atlast 0 Skip to Content About Method MY Super Ingredient Open Menu Close Menu About Method MY Super Ingredient Open Menu Close Menu About Method MY Super Ingredient Mycelium = Mushroom Wanna hear a secret? At Atlast we look to nature for inspiration — we call it the “Forager’s ” Specialty gourmet mushrooms like Chicken of the Woods, Beefsteak Polypore, Lion’s Mane and others are already coveted by chefs for their taste and The challenge is that these mushrooms are often foraged in the woods at specific times of the year, take a tremendous amount of time to grow and they come in strange mushroomy Chicken of the Woods Beefsteak Polypore What we’ve done is figure out how to domesticate specialty mushrooms and grow them in huge slabs at commercial Instead of raising livestock in pastures or crops in fields, we tend to mycelium - the root of all fungi - via indoor farms to create whole, delicious cuts of what we call “MY super ” Using our mycelium super ingredient, we are able to make mushroom meat that competes with traditional meat cuts in both texture and flavor without complicated added Atlast sells MY (short for mycelium) super ingredient directly to other food companies so more people can get tasty in their hands and on supermarket Partner with us Maximum Nutrition Whole Food MY super ingredient has a naturally high nutritional profile Our secret is in our proprietary growth process, not the DNA Our process uses less water compared to traditional pork production Allergen Free Big 8 allergen free— no gluten, soy, shellfish, eggs, fish, dairy, or nuts Amino Acids Contains all 9 essential amino acids making MY super ingredient a complete source of protein Versatile We’ve transformed our super ingredient into bacon, pasta, chicken , the list goes on! , September 9, PRNewswire — PAQ Therapeutics (“PAQ”), a biotechnology company harnessing the power of autophagy to restore health and cure disease, and Insilico Medicine (“Insilico”), an artificial intelligence (AI)-driven drug discovery company, today announced that the companies have entered into a collaboration agreement to develop small molecule therapies designed to hijack the autophagy pathway to address novel disease Under the terms of the agreement, both parties will leverage Insilico’s small molecule compound generation platform Chemistry42 and other drug discovery technologies in combination with PAQ’s compound (ATTEC) technology platform to discover novel small molecules with the potential to catalyze and selectively enhance the degradation of entities through Autophagy is the natural cellular degradation mechanism that removes unnecessary or dysfunctional components through a With its powerful ATTEC technology platform, PAQ expands the therapeutic potential of autophagy to target not only proteins, but also lipids, pathogens, and other substrates with the goal of restoring Insilico’s drug discovery platforms utilize deep generative models, reinforcement learning, transformers, and other modern machine learning techniques to speed the generation of new molecular structures with specific properties, improving the efficiency and success of drug “PAQ’s approach supports a pivotal moment in the evolution of drug discovery and design by expanding the ability to target the substrates underlying diseases with limited or no treatment options,” said Feng Ren, , Chief Scientific Officer and Head of Drug R&D at “Insilico is pleased to partner with PAQ Therapeutics to leverage our drug discovery platforms in advancing drug R&D of ATTECs to address unmet medical ” “As part of PAQ’s ongoing efforts to therapeutically harness degradation, one key next step is to integrate technologies like AI that support our overall and drug discovery strategy,” said Nan Ji, , , President and CEO, PAQ “We are excited to leverage Insilico’s deep expertise and proven track record in drug discovery during a pivotal time in our company’s growth and ” About Insilico Medicine Insilico Medicine, an artificial drug discovery company, is developing artificial intelligence These platforms use deep generative models, reinforcement learning, transformers, and other modern machine learning techniques for novel target discovery and the generation of novel molecular structures with desired Insilico Medicine is developing breakthrough solutions to discover and develop innovative drugs for cancer, fibrosis, infectious diseases, autoimmune diseases, and For more information, visit . About PAQ Therapeutics PAQ Therapeutics is a biotechnology company pioneering a new approach to restoring heath and curing disease through autophagy, the body’s most versatile mechanism for natural cellular With our ATTEC (autophagosome-tethering compound) technology, we are developing a novel class of small molecule degraders capable of binding a diverse array of substrates to the autophagy PAQ’s research advances are driving an important new class of degradation therapies with the potential to fundamentally transform drug discovery and development and target a range of substrates including proteins, aggregates, lipids, organelles, and For more information, visit . sidebar PAQ Therapeutics Mass Office Cambridge, MA, , USA Privacy Policy Terms and Conditions © PAQ All rights   PAQ | Harnessing the Power of Autophagy Skip to primary navigation Skip to main content PAQ Approach Our Technology Our Team Join Us News & Media Contact Us Harnessing the Power of Autophagy to Restore Health and Cure Disease PAQ Approach PAQ’s global team is pioneering a new approach to restoring health and curing disease through autophagy, the body’s most versatile mechanism for natural cellular We are developing a new class of small molecule degradation therapies by expanding the ability to directly target and eliminate entities beyond Our Technology PAQ’s platform is driven by compounds (ATTECs), small molecules with the potential to catalyze and selectively enhance the degradation of entities through Using this powerful platform, PAQ has the potential to identify and design novel therapies to deliver on the promise of autophagy with the goal of overcoming serious diseases that have limited or no treatment PAQ’s initial focus is on a genetic neurodegenerative disorder with no current treatment options for PAQ plans to expand the ATTEC platform to target additional protein and Our Team PAQ’s expert team

Engineers then review the detections, add annotations to those that are valid, mark false positives and geotag them to specific locations on drawings of the Orthomosaics Since most orthomosaics (stitched composite images) provide a complete representation of a façade or roof, they don’t include separate T2D2 applies orthomosaic models using a “sliding window” approach to mark damage and prevent of conditions on images with overlapping Condition Assessment Reports T2D2’s secure online portal maintains a record of all detected damage and associated metadata, including engineer reviews, and can generate reports that serve as a basis for repair Videos T2D2 evaluates the individual frames of videos, tracking detections across multiple frames to filter out false Models Drone surveys of buildings often produce photogrammetric T2D2 performs damage detection on the original images and geotags the model using the mapping from the photogrammetry The T2D2 portal lets you interact with the model containing the associated Thermography T2D2 processes thermographic images to detect anomalies such as leaks and moisture entrapment in façades and o Panotours T2D2 processes panoramic tours
